Diarrhea is an increase in the the volume, wateriness and or frequency of bowel movements.

Diarrhea has many causes, but can usually diagnosed and treated by talking to a medical professional. Causes of diarrhea differ depending on time. Less than 2 weeks (acute) or greater than 2 weeks (chronic). Acute causes or more commonly seen.

Acute watery diarrhea in an otherwise healthy person may be self-limited, however, explosive diarrhea and acute bloody diarrhea require medical management ASAP. Diarrhea may present with vomiting, fever, and bloating. Dehydration is a great concern in a patient with diarrhea as it can be life threatening is severe cases. If you are having diarrhea severely, Schedule a visit now with a Medical Professional that can evaluate and treat you immediately.
If Diarrhea is interfering with your daily life, log on AITMED and talk to a doctor to receive a treatment plan customized for you.
